101 |title = Narayanhity Royal Palace, home of the King of Nepal |page = 14 |url = https://books.google.com/?id=N2kKAQAAIAAJ|publisher = His Majesty's Govt., Ministry of Communications, Dept. of Information |year = 1975}}\n* Watters, Thomas. (1904\u201305). ''On Yuan Chwang's Travels in India. (629\u2013645 CE).'' Royal Asiatic Society. Second Indian Edition. Munshhiram Manoharlal Publishers, New Delhi. (1973).\n* {{Cite book |last = Woodhatch |first = Tom |title = Nepal handbook |page = [https://archive.org/details/nepalhandbook0000wood/page/194 194] |work = The Royal Palace |accessdate = 17 December 2009 |url = https://archive.org/details/nepalhandbook0000wood |url-access = registration |publisher = Footprint Travel Guides |year = 1999 |isbn = 978-1-900949-44-6 }}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140819083413/http://www.turkishairlines.com/en-int/corporate/news/news/turkish-airlines-launches-a-new-route-to-kathmandu]\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikivoyage}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{osmrelation-inline|4583125}}\n{{List of Asian capitals by region}}\n{{Kathmandu District}}\n{{Newar}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Kathmandu| ]]<!--please leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:Cities in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Capitals in Asia]]\n[[Category:Metropolitan cities in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Metropolitan areas of Nepal]]\n[[Category:Municipalities in Bagmati Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Kathmandu District]]\n[[Category:Hill stations in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Newar]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Nepal municipalities established in 1953]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Capital of Nepal}}\n{{About|Kathmandu Metropolitan City}}\n{{Use British English Oxford spelling|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Kathmandu<br>{{small|Kastamandap (ancient name)}}\n| native_name                     = \u0915\u093e\u0920\u092e\u093e\u0921\u094c\u0902\n|